		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But you should know at least one language used for making PC programs, even if only to make the tools for converting data to be used by your NES programs.</div>
<br />Celius and Memblers seem to like making their tools for the NES itself. After all, if we use PC tools to make PC programs, why not on the NES? =)
<br />
<br />Seriously, I know that some things just can't be done on the NES. My BMP to level map converter is a pretty good example, as it works with images as big as 20MB. and editing everything tile by tile on the NES would be a pain in the ass.
<br />
<br />So yeah, I agree that knowing how to program for a PC does help a lot.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
